
Step1:
Create springboot with mysql crud application

Step2: Add dependency in pom.xml
1)spring-boot-starter-data-redis
2)spring-boot-starter-cache

Step3: Add th configuration details in application.properties or yml file
spring.cache.type=redis
# Do not cache nulls
#spring.cache.redis.cache-null-values=false
# 10 minutes default TTL
spring.cache.redis.time-to-live=600000ms
spring.cache.redis.use-key-prefix=true
spring.cache.redis.key-prefix="CACHE_"
spring.data.redis.host=localhost
spring.data.redis.port=6379
# if we are using local redis or cloud but here we use docker so there is no need of username or password
spring.data.redis.username=
spring.data.redis.password=
logging.level.org.springframework.data.redis=DEBUG

Step4:
Enable cache annotations in service class, whatever method you want cache.

private static final String CACHE_NAME = "cache_users";

@Cacheable(value = CACHE_NAME, key = "#id")
getUser(Long id) {}

@CachePut(value = CACHE_NAME, key = "#user.id")
createUser(User user) {}

@CachePut(value = CACHE_NAME, key = "#user.id")
updateUser(User user) {}

@CacheEvict(value = CACHE_NAME, key = "#id")
deleteUser(Long id)

Step5: Run the Redis cache
update the redis cmd: docker pull redis:latest
run the redis cmd: docker run -d --name my-redis-cache-01 -p 6379:6379 redis:latest
verify the container cmd: docker ps

Step6: test the endpoints
I was enabled getUser endpoint, when i hit the first time checking the cache,
there is no record will execute the database query and stored in to cache.
In a second hit onwards, fetching the values from cache.
***Monitor the logs query was not executed while fetching the data from cache.

